:::summary
Geology is the science of the Earth — its materials, structures, processes, and history. By studying rocks, minerals, fossils, and the forces that shape landscapes, geologists have reconstructed billions of years of Earth's past and mapped the physical foundations on which all life depends. For Christians, geology raises profound questions about creation, time, and the relationship between scientific and scriptural accounts of origins — questions that have generated some of the richest dialogue between faith and science in modern history.
:::

